n probe quadratic gravity from black\nhole quadrupole moment measurements of black hole-pulsars. We find that bounds\non the parity-violating sector of quadratic gravity can be stronger than\ncurrent bounds by six orders of magnitude. These results suggest that a new\ndiscovery of black hole-pulsars in the future will provide powerful ways to\nprobe gravity further.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 31 Jul 2018 21:57:17 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 4 Dec 2018 00:17:12 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sat, 21 Mar 2020 19:16:21 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-03-24"}
